1.0.0 SNAPSHOT
==============
- Fixed incoming stats tracking algorithm issue that caused cookied users to be tracked incorrectly (May 25, 2008)
- Fixed bug in the hourly stats update routine that could generate a MySQL error message (May 27, 2008)
- Fixed issue in the General Settings interface that caused the Return Percent value to be multiplied by 100 (May 27, 2008)
- Improved the software's ability to locate the CLI version of PHP on the server (May 30, 2008)
- Fixed issue with blank ranking page when using certain sorting options and having minhits > 0 (June 14, 2008)
- Fixed issue with the in.php script that would prevent page rendering when used in a PHP virtual() call (June 30, 2008)
- Fixed control panel JavaScript errors in IE7 (June 30, 2008)
- Updated Statistical Tracking Overview documentation with more universal code for .php pages when using embedded tracking (June 30, 2008)
- Removed warning message when saving ranking page templates that use the {$icon} template variable (June 30, 2008)
- Updated Ranking Page Templates documentation with additional available options for the order setting of the {accounts} template function (June 30, 2008)
- Added new stats attribute to the {accounts} template function to allow pulling of more detailed statistical information for each account (June 30, 2008)
- Updated default template to display both incoming and outgoing stats for each account (June 30, 2008)
- Fixed issue with account editing interface reporting an invalid banner file type (July 29, 2008)
- Fixed issue with SQL having clause not being properly generated for some {accounts} template functions (July 30, 2008)
- Fixed issue with banner data not being properly updated when serving banners (July 30, 2008)
- Updated display of edited account data to not include the banner data or local banner URL (August 4, 2008)
- Updated documentation to replace incorrect {$category.page_url} value with {$category.filename} (August 4, 2008)
- Fixed issue with duplicate ratings generating MySQL error message (August 20, 2008)
- Updated the skimming system to better determine when a click should be sent to a trade or to the URL provided (January 13, 2009)
- Added setting for the HTTP status code used when redirecting surfers through the out.php script (January 20, 2009)
- Fixed issue with the inactive count not being properly maintained (January 20, 2009)
- Fixed issue that allowed a surfer to only rate one account (February 14, 2009)
- Updated patch.php script to automatically handle database inconsistency possible with previous snapshot release (March 2, 2008)
- Fixed issue with comment flood protection (via the Comment Interval setting) not working properly (March 20, 2009)
- Fixed issue with filler ranks not being displayed correctly when the number of accounts is one less than the number to display (April 12, 2009)
- Fixed error in the default accounts-edit.tpl template that prevented display of the banner size limits (April 17, 2009)
- Fixed issue that allowed incorrectly sized banners to be submitted (May 12, 2009)
- Removed requirement of Zend Optimizer (March 22, 2010)
- Removed requirement of OpenSSL extension (March 22, 2010)
- Software now provided completely as source with no encoded files (March 22, 2010)
- Improved support for PHP 5.3 (April 15, 2010)
- Fixed issue that could prevent user defined account fields from being updated by end-users (November 21, 2010)

	Modified Files
	--------------
	For reference only; may be incomplete! Use software manual patching instructions to update your installation



